The paper proposes a new graph neural network model for node and graph classification, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper also discusses the properties of graph convolution and graph-level pooling, which are relevant to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
